42 'state minimum standard codes' shall have the same meaning as in paragraph (9) of Code
43 Section 8-2-20; and
44 (3) Provide that for each new elementary school constructed on or after July 1, 2027,
45 which includes a playground, such playground shall meet the following design standards:
46 (A) Provides a sensory-diverse environment that enables children of all abilities to
47 develop physically, socially, and emotionally;
48 (B) Provides an engaging play space with age and ability-appropriate levels of
49 challenge and offers opportunities for children of all abilities to succeed, regardless of
50 physical and intellectual attributes;
51 (C) Enables all students to benefit from state mandated recess time for elementary
52 students;
53 (D) Capable for use as an outdoor classroom that is open to all students; and
54 (E) Meets the following minimum guidelines:
55 (i) Playground is accessible via a sidewalk or pathway from the school;
56 (ii) Playground is a minimum of 10,000 square feet in area;
57 (iii) Fencing surrounds and encloses the entire playground area;
58 (iv) A minimum of 20 percent of the total playground area shall be shaded; provided,
59 however, that such shaded area may comprise more than one area so long as the total
60 shaded area meets or exceeds 20 percent of the total playground area; and, provided,
61 further, that such shading may be provided by natural means, such as existing mature
62 trees, or man-made means, such as sun canopies;
63 (v) Unitary surfacing shall be used throughout at least 80 percent of the playground
64 area. Examples of unitary surfacing include, but are not limited to, turf, bonded
65 rubber, and poured in place rubber; and
66 (vi) Multiple components that are installed on a portion of the playground with the
67 unitary surfacing and are accessible for all users that address the physical, sensory,
